<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="755">Diagnosis A large, spectacularly distinct species whose major has a huge spherical head, proportionately reduced clypeus and mandibles, a mesonotum that drops vertically in side view to the metanotum, and a near-absence of pilosity on the head and mesosoma.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
